React Native Project - README

Getting Started

Follow these steps to set up and run the project:

1. Start the Metro Server

Metro is the tool that bundles your JavaScript code for React Native. To start it, open a terminal in the project directory and run:

npm start

Leave this terminal running while working on the app.

2. Run the App

Open a new terminal in the project directory:

For Android:

npm run android

3. Edit the App

Open the App.tsx file in your preferred code editor.

Make your changes.

Refresh the app to see updates:

Android: Press R twice in the terminal or use the Developer Menu (Ctrl + M for Windows/Linux or Cmd + M for macOS).

4. Environment Variables

To use GitHub API features:

Create a .env file in the project directory.

Add your GitHub personal access token:

GITHUB_TOKEN=your_personal_access_token

5. Testing the App on Android Devices

If you want to test the app on a physical Android device:

Build an APK using Gradle or Android Studio.

Install the APK on your device.